ImGuiTestLogFlags_.name: ImGuiTestLogFlags_NoHeader
ImGuiTestLogFlags_.comment: // Do not display frame count and depth padding

ImGuiTestAction.name: ImGuiTestAction_Check
ImGuiTestAction.comment: // Check item if unchecked (Checkbox, MenuItem or any widget reporting ImGuiItemStatusFlags_Checkable)

ImGuiTestAction.name: ImGuiTestAction_Open
ImGuiTestAction.comment: // Open item if closed (TreeNode, BeginMenu or any widget reporting ImGuiItemStatusFlags_Openable)

ImGuiTestAction.name: ImGuiTestAction_Input
ImGuiTestAction.comment: // Start text inputing into a field (e.g. CTRL+Click on Drags/Slider, click on InputText etc.)

ImGuiCaptureFlags_.name: ImGuiCaptureFlags_StitchAll
ImGuiCaptureFlags_.comment: // Capture entire window scroll area (by scrolling and taking multiple screenshot). Only works for a single window.

ImGuiCaptureFlags_.name: ImGuiCaptureFlags_IncludeOtherWindows
ImGuiCaptureFlags_.comment: // Disable hiding other windows (when CaptureAddWindow has been called by default other windows are hidden)

ImGuiCaptureFlags_.name: ImGuiCaptureFlags_IncludePopups
ImGuiCaptureFlags_.comment: // Expand capture area to automatically include visible popups (Unused if ImGuiCaptureFlags_IncludeOtherWindows is set)

ImGuiCaptureFlags_.name: ImGuiCaptureFlags_HideMouseCursor
ImGuiCaptureFlags_.comment: // Hide render software mouse cursor during capture.

ImGuiCaptureFlags_.name: ImGuiCaptureFlags_Instant
ImGuiCaptureFlags_.comment: // Perform capture on very same frame. Only works when capturing a rectangular region. Unsupported features: content stitching, window hiding, window relocation.

ImGuiTestOpFlags_.name: ImGuiTestOpFlags_NoCheckHoveredId
ImGuiTestOpFlags_.comment: // Don't check for HoveredId after aiming for a widget. A few situations may want this: while e.g. dragging or another items prevents hovering, or for items that don't use ItemHoverable()

ImGuiTestOpFlags_.name: ImGuiTestOpFlags_NoError
ImGuiTestOpFlags_.comment: // Don't abort/error e.g. if the item cannot be found or the operation doesn't succeed.

ImGuiTestOpFlags_.name: ImGuiTestOpFlags_NoFocusWindow
ImGuiTestOpFlags_.comment: // Don't focus window when aiming at an item

ImGuiTestOpFlags_.name: ImGuiTestOpFlags_NoAutoUncollapse
ImGuiTestOpFlags_.comment: // Disable automatically uncollapsing windows (useful when specifically testing Collapsing behaviors)

ImGuiTestOpFlags_.name: ImGuiTestOpFlags_NoAutoOpenFullPath
ImGuiTestOpFlags_.comment: // Disable automatically opening intermediaries (e.g. ItemClick("Hello/OK") will automatically first open "Hello" if "OK" isn't found. Only works if ref is a string path.

ImGuiTestOpFlags_.name: ImGuiTestOpFlags_NoYield
ImGuiTestOpFlags_.comment: // Don't yield (only supported by a few functions), in case you need to manage rigorous per-frame timing.

ImGuiTestOpFlags_.name: ImGuiTestOpFlags_IsSecondAttempt
ImGuiTestOpFlags_.comment: // Used by recursing functions to indicate a second attempt

ImGuiTestOpFlags_.name: ImGuiTestOpFlags_MoveToEdgeL
ImGuiTestOpFlags_.comment: // Simple Dumb aiming helpers to test widget that care about clicking position. May need to replace will better functionalities.

ImGuiTestRunSpeed.name: ImGuiTestRunSpeed_Fast
ImGuiTestRunSpeed.comment: // Run tests as fast as possible (teleport mouse, skip delays, etc.)

ImGuiTestRunSpeed.name: ImGuiTestRunSpeed_Normal
ImGuiTestRunSpeed.comment: // Run tests at human watchable speed (for debugging)

ImGuiTestRunSpeed.name: ImGuiTestRunSpeed_Cinematic
ImGuiTestRunSpeed.comment: // Run tests with pauses between actions (for e.g. tutorials)

ImGuiTestRunFlags_.name: ImGuiTestRunFlags_GuiFuncDisable
ImGuiTestRunFlags_.comment: // Used internally to temporarily disable the GUI func (at the end of a test, etc)

ImGuiTestRunFlags_.name: ImGuiTestRunFlags_GuiFuncOnly
ImGuiTestRunFlags_.comment: // Set when user selects "Run GUI func"

ImGuiTestRunFlags_.name: ImGuiTestRunFlags_EnableRawInputs
ImGuiTestRunFlags_.comment: // Disable input submission to let test submission raw input event (in order to test e.g. IO queue)

ImGuiTestRunFlags_.name: ImGuiTestRunFlags_RunFromGui
ImGuiTestRunFlags_.comment: // Test ran manually from GUI, will disable watchdog.

ImGuiTestRunFlags_.name: ImGuiTestRunFlags_ShareVars
ImGuiTestRunFlags_.comment: // Share generic vars and custom vars between child and parent tests (custom vars need to be same type)

ImGuiTestRunFlags_.name: ImGuiTestRunFlags_ShareTestContext
ImGuiTestRunFlags_.comment: // Share ImGuiTestContext instead of creating a new one (unsure what purpose this may be useful for yet)

ImGuiPerfToolDisplayType.name: ImGuiPerfToolDisplayType_Simple
ImGuiPerfToolDisplayType.comment: // Each run will be displayed individually.

ImGuiPerfToolDisplayType.name: ImGuiPerfToolDisplayType_PerBranchColors
ImGuiPerfToolDisplayType.comment: // Use one bar color per branch.

ImGuiPerfToolDisplayType.name: ImGuiPerfToolDisplayType_CombineByBuildInfo
ImGuiPerfToolDisplayType.comment: // Entries with same build information will be averaged.

ImGuiTestFlags_.name: ImGuiTestFlags_NoGuiWarmUp
ImGuiTestFlags_.comment: // Disable running the GUI func for 2 frames before starting test code. For tests which absolutely need to start before GuiFunc.

ImGuiTestFlags_.name: ImGuiTestFlags_NoAutoFinish
ImGuiTestFlags_.comment: // By default, tests with no TestFunc (only a GuiFunc) will end after warmup. Setting this require test to call ctx->Finish().

ImGuiTestFlags_.name: ImGuiTestFlags_NoRecoveryWarnings
ImGuiTestFlags_.comment: // Error/recovery warnings (missing End/Pop calls etc.) will be displayed as normal debug entries, for tests which may rely on those.
